## UI/UX Guidelines
- Maintain consistency with the design system: typography scales, color tokens, spacing, and component variants.
- Ensure responsive behavior for desktop and mobile; editors remain usable on smaller viewports.
- Provide clear affordances for saving, snapshots, and exporting.
- Display progress indicators during AI generation and export operations.
- Accessibility: keyboard navigable, screen-reader friendly labeling, and contrasting colors for readability.

---

## Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety

CRITICAL: Follow these rules in ALL generated code to prevent runtime crashes.

1) Supabase query results:
   - Always use nullish coalescing — const items = data ?? [].
   - Example: const analyses = (data?.analyses ?? []) as Analysis[];

2) Array methods:
   - Guard before invoking: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].

3) React useState for arrays/objects:
   - Initialize properly: const [sections, setSections] = useState<SectionContent[]>([]);

4) API response shapes:
   - Validate: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [];

5) Optional chaining:
   - Use obj?.property?.nested when accessing nested API results.

6) Destructuring with defaults:
   - const { sections = [], health = 0 } = response ?? {};

---

## Example Data Flows (High-Level)

- When the user edits a section:
  - Frontend calls POST /analyses/:id/sections/:sectionKey/edit with { content }.
  - Server validates, updates SectionContent, and returns updated content.
  - Frontend updates local state and pushes a new Snapshot if requested.

- When generating AI analysis:
  - Frontend calls POST /analyses/:id/ai/generate with { depthLevel, benchmarks }.
  - AIAnalysisEngine compiles prompts for each section, calls AI model(s), returns structured payload.
  - Server caches results; frontend renders sections and updates health scores.

- When exporting PDF:
  - Frontend calls POST /analyses/:id/export/pdf with branding options.
  - PDFExportService enqueues job if needed; returns exportId.
  - Client polls GET /exports/:exportId/status; on completion, GET /exports/:exportId/download.

- Health scoring:
  - On analysis completion or on-demand, GET /analyses/:id/health computes and returns overall and sub-scores. UI displays HealthScorePanel.

